cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with packet routing and buffer space requirements in networks. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses tradeoffs between speed and buffer space, which can be analyzed using information theory. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper proposes algorithms for buffer management. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is possible as the paper considers the number of distinct destinations in the network. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is also possible as the paper analyzes the performance of the network in terms of buffer space requirements.
